{"questionId":"9309","questionHtml":"<p>A continuous random variable <em>X</em> has the probability density function <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\left\\{ {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{{36}}{\\text{sin}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{6}} \\right){\\text{,}}}&amp;{0 \\leqslant x \\leqslant 6} \\\\   {0{\\text{,}}}&amp;{{\\text{otherwise}}}  \\end{array}} \\right.\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>{</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mi>π</mi>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mn>36</mn>\n                </mrow>\n              </mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mtext>sin</mtext>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <mo>(</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mfrac>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mi>π</mi>\n                      <mi>x</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mn>6</mn>\n                  </mfrac>\n                </mrow>\n                <mo>)</mo>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <mtext>,</mtext>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n              <mo>⩽</mo>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mo>⩽</mo>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <mtext>,</mtext>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <mtext>otherwise</mtext>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Find P(0 ≤ <em>X</em> ≤ 3).</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempting integration by parts, <em>eg</em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"u = \\frac{{\\pi x}}{{36}}{\\text{,}}\\,{\\text{d}}u = \\frac{\\pi }{{36}}{\\text{d}}x{\\text{,}}\\,{\\text{d}}v = {\\text{sin}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{6}} \\right){\\text{d}}x{\\text{,}}\\,v =&nbsp; - \\frac{6}{\\pi }{\\text{cos}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{6}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>u</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>36</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>u</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>36</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>π</mi>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>d</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>π</mi>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>&nbsp;(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>P(0 ≤&nbsp;<em>X</em>&nbsp;≤ 3)&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{\\pi }{{36}}\\left( {\\left[ { - \\frac{{6x}}{\\pi }{\\text{cos}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{6}} \\right)} \\right]_0^3 + \\frac{6}{\\pi }\\int\\limits_0^3 {{\\text{cos}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{6}} \\right)} {\\text{d}}x} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>36</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msubsup>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>6</mn>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mi>π</mi>\n            </mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>cos</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mi>π</mi>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mn>6</mn>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </msubsup>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n      </mfrac>\n      <munderover>\n        <mo>∫</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </munderover>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>cos</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>π</mi>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>&nbsp; A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for a correct <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"uv\">\n  <mi>u</mi>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span> and <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for a correct&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int {v\\,{\\text{d}}u} \">\n  <mo>∫</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>d</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>u</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>attempting to substitute limits&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{\\pi }{{36}}\\left[ { - \\frac{{6x}}{\\pi }{\\text{cos}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{6}} \\right)} \\right]_0^3 = 0\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>36</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>[</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>6</mn>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>π</mi>\n        </mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>cos</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>π</mi>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>]</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;P(0 ≤&nbsp;<em>X</em>&nbsp;≤ 3)&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{1}{\\pi }\\left[ {{\\text{sin}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\pi x}}{6}} \\right)} \\right]_0^3\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>[</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>sin</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>π</mi>\n                <mi>x</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>]</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msubsup>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(or equivalent) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{1}{\\pi }\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9309","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.7","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"A continuous random variable X has the probability density function f given by f ( x ) = { π x 36 sin ( π x 6 ) , 0 ⩽ x ⩽ 6 0 , otherwise . Find P(0 ≤ X ≤ 3).","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"7","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Properties of discrete and continuous random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}